</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3116523FFA7A507CFEBC2A5FE47A5A4" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB436A8FFA7A507CFEBC2A5FE47A5A4" blockId="30.[151,1436,152,903]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFA7A507CFEBC2A5FEA0A52C" bold="true" box="[198,313,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</emphasis>
One of the specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFA7A507CD57C2A5FCB3A52D" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[634,810,757,782]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="geographus">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFA7A507CD57C2A5FCB3A52D" box="[634,810,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. geographus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Pamban resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFA7A507CBFAC2A5FA0DA52D" authorityName="Petuch" authorityYear="1979" box="[1239,1428,757,782]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fragilissimus">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFA7A507CBFAC2A5FA0DA52D" box="[1239,1428,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">C. fragilissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, comparatively thinner and with sharp outer lip compared to other specimens (Figure 62M). The restricted distribution of this species to the 
<collectingRegion id="49CFF84AFFA7A507CED7C315FDB6A57C" box="[506,559,837,863]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Gulf</collectingRegion>
of Mannar could be due to its preference for corals and sand bottoms with appropriate prey organisms.
</paragraph>
